===Etymology===
[[Category:Greek derivations]]
From [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[ονοματοποιία]]''' (''onomatopoiia'') "the coining of a word in imitation of a sound", from '''[[ονοματοποιέω]]''' (''onomatopoieo'') "to coin names", from '''[[όνομα]]''' (''onoma'') "name" + '''[[ποιέω]]''' (''poieo'') "to make, to do, to produce".
===Noun===
'''onomatopoeia''' (''[[countable]] and [[uncountable]]'')

#(''[[uncountable]]'') The property of a word of sounding like what it represents.
#(''[[countable]]'') A [[word]] which has the property of onomatopoeia, such as "moo" or "hiss".

